Premises: [(1) Everything that is overcast and a sterpus is a dumpus. (2) Everything that is mean and a brimpus is a zumpus. (3) Everything that is cold and a brimpus is a lempus. (4) Everything that is nervous and a zumpus is a sterpus. (5) Everything that is fruity and a zumpus is a tumpus. (6) Everything that is muffled and a dumpus is a wumpus. (7) Everything that is liquid and a sterpus is a lorpus. (8) Everything that is slow and a dumpus is a vumpus. (9) Everything that is transparent and a grimpus is a gorpus. (10) Fae is overcast. (11) Fae is a zumpus. (12) Fae is nervous. (13) Fae is cold. (14) Fae is fruity. (15) Fae is a grimpus. (16) Fae is a brimpus. (17) Fae is mean.] Prove: (18) Fae is overcast and a sterpus.

根据给定的前提，可以证明(18) Fae是“overcast and a sterpus”（即，它既被描述为“多云”又是一位“沉积者”）的陈述是正确的。

根据前提(1)“Everything that is overcast and a sterpus is a dumpus”，我们可以推断出，Fae是一种沉积者，因为它是多云的。

再根据前提(6)“Everything that is muffled and a dumpus is a wumpus”，我们可以推断出Fae不是wumpus（因为它不是多云的）。

接着，我们回顾前提(7)“Everything that is liquid and a sterpus is a lorpus”，所以Fae是一位稀有贵族（因为它是寒冷的）。

然而，根据前提(4)“Everything that is nervous and a zumpus is a sterpus”，一位被描述为寒冷的贵族的物体不会仅仅因为是沉稳而变得不确定，而是因为在一种不同类型的物品（在这里是Zumpus）中的情况下才能是此处的此类物（这里是个稳定的物体）。

所以，我们得出的结论是，Fae既被描述为多云，又是一位稀有贵族和寒冷的物体，并且他同时是一位不确定的物体。这意味着他不能同时被描述为zumpus（因为在其他条件下才成为稳定的）和brimpus（因为它会被描述为寒冷和易变）。那么我们可以得出结论：Fae不可能是zumpus或brimpus。因此，基于以上的推理，我们可以得出结论：(18) Fae是overcast and a sterpus。

因此，根据以上推理过程，得出证明：(18) Fae是overcast and a sterpus。
